text: Israeli startup Remilk, one of the world’s leading companies in cultured milk, will launch its animal-free milk in Israeli stores starting January 2026. Remilk uses fermentation to produce dairy proteins that are identical to cow’s milk- but made entirely without cows

Israel's “Gift of Life” organization tried to register a world record celebrating 2,000 altruistic kidney donors who saved strangers' lives. Guinness accepted the fees, reviewed the materials, and then abruptly announced it no longer processes submissions from Israel.
Israeli researchers believe they may have isolated the 'Holy Grail' cells which can slow down aging. 'T helper' blood cells may hold the secret to longevity.
